history.content:
<md>> I filled out my Computer Science Major Appeals and Exceptions Requests form on May 10th to satisfy my Math 53 requirement from Community College. Is there anything I can do? 

Try emailing an advisor to check on the status if it's been that long, doesn't hurt to send a polite email asking if they received it!
> Also, I was wondering whether the upper division AC class I took be counted towards my L&S college 36-unit upper division unit requirement?

Yep it should!</md>

The faculty member in charge of exception meetings has been taking a break, so we have not been having as many meetings as normal. We'll be sure to get to your exception request, but you can certainly ping us at cs-advising@cs.berkeley.edu if you're worried that we've skipped over you.
